  "title": "Network Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Design and deploy functional networks (LAN, WAN, WLAN, SDWAN).</li>\n  <li>Configure and install routers, switches, wireless, SDWAN and other network devices.</li>\n  <li>Monitor network performance and troubleshoot issues.</li>\n  <li>Ensure network connectivity and performance across all company systems.</li>\n  <li>Provide onsite support for the Campus and Data Center.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with network team members on network optimization and scaling.</li>\n  <li>Maintain accurate documentation of network configurations, procedures, and service records.</li>\n  <li>Provide Level 4/5 support and troubleshooting to resolve issues.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with vendors and other IT personnel for problem resolution.</li>\n  <li>Stay current with industry trends and emerging technologies.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Minimum Qualifications</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field (or equivalent experience).</li>\n  <li>5-10 years related work experience with proven experience as a Network Engineer.</li>\n  <li>Valid CCNP or CCIE Certificate in Enterprise Network or Data Center.</li>\n  <li>Solid understanding of network operating systems (Cisco IOS, Wireless, Arista EOS, SDWAN..., etc.).</li>\n  <li>Hands-on experience with monitoring, network diagnostic and network analytics tools.</li>\n  <li>Strong knowledge of networking technologies (routing, switching, firewalls, VPNs).</li>\n  <li>Experience with Cisco, Arista hardware.</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with cloud networking (AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud) is a plus.</li>\n</ul>",
